        "sender": "w-nws.webmaster@noaa.gov",
        "senderName": "NWS Fairbanks AK",
        "headline": "Winter Weather Advisory issued June 7 at 3:35PM AKDT until June 8 at 10:00PM AKDT by NWS Fairbanks AK",
        "description": "* WHAT...Snow. Total snow accumulations between 4 and 8 inches.\nWinds gusting as high as 30 mph at Atigun Pass.\n\n* WHERE...Central Brooks Range.\n\n* WHEN...Until 10 PM AKDT Monday.\n\n* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult. Gusty winds could lead to\nareas of blowing snow which could significantly reduce visibility.\n\n* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Heaviest snow totals are expected across the\nsouthern Arctic Plains and northern slopes of the Brooks Range.",
        "instruction": "Slow down and use caution while traveling. Visit 511.alaska.gov or\ncall 5 1 1 for the latest road conditions.",
